snippet.textDisplay:
Lyrics Translation:- 🔥🦋🔥🎯
What must I do and what I mustn't,
DON'T tell me 
You can’t force mehendi on my hands. 
(consent can not be forcefully sought)
In the path of my happiness, why do you wrought thorns?
When I sing in front of the world,
You don’t even applaud.
What do you have to say about your own state-of-mind and your questions/doubts/ your delimmas?
When I am my own companion, then why should I bother about you or anyone.
I hold my dreams in my fist.
I have drowned my tears in a twist,
Seeing me return with such bravery, the entire universe sings joyfully...
Here comes she!
Here comes she!
I came out victoriously!
Yeah
(Mangi on the mic)
My tribe is standing, waiting for me
Holding candles in their hands, they’re sure *here I’ll be* (conquering/ forthcoming) 

Just as one night returned, Ho Jamalo 
(light of God, unwavering, unfettered)
Like a single human, epitomizes the entire race’s bravery
Come, now show your spark!
What are you waiting for? Your caravan stands behind you to follow your path,
Whatever sorrows you have, just shove them out of your heart.
Who will stop you, you do your part ;)
What I say is worth millions,
These days, success is just a game of  chance,
This vanity will yield nothing.
Ask me, I take a fair and just stance
Sing what’s in your heart. Whatever you want to be, become that.
Here, everything is limitless
This world runs on dreams. From intent, I carved out my journey.
Rest.. Life goes on, It will never cease.
Open your eyes dear, Till when will you remain asleep?
Caged in your thoughts; how will you ever soar and kiss the skies?
When the beat drops, will you then finally take to the floor?
Flung out of space helplessly like a nickel, spiraling & swaying on the floor!?
I hold my dreams in my fist,
I have drowned my tears in a twist,
Upon seeing me return with such resilience, the entire universe sings in joy,
Here comes she!
I couldn't sleep peacefully, while my kin rested on cold floors,
I therefore fulfilled my dreams, I'm no longer a slave to 'cash flow,
All the lights on me, upon the stage I be,
Here comes she!
My friends, the sun has risen,
Dark days are over,
My victory has arrived from her prison
Her shyness is forsaken,
Giving *hope* to dreams...
The people of Thar were awakened,
In the caravan, she’s not alone,
Accompanying her are the commoners from mud homes,
Such is the philosophy of life ;)
And still, this isn’t the end of strife
Seeing me return with such resilience, the entire universe sings in joy,
Here comes she!
Here comes she!
Look she’s come victoriously!
